posts.title: Female Honduran illegal alien, Any Belloza, who attended Babson College deported when she tries to board a flight from Boston to Texas to see her family. These types of illegals, young women, mooching off of us should be prioritized for deportation much moreso than cartel members.

link_metadata.description: A college freshman trying to fly from Boston to Texas to surprise her family for Thanksgiving was deported to Honduras in violation of a court order. That’s according to an attorney for Any Lucia Lopez Belloza, a 19-year-old at Babson College. She was detained by immigration officials at Boston Logan International Airport on November 20. A federal judge issued an emergency order the day after her arrest prohibiting the government from removing her from Massachusetts for 72 hours. However, within two days, she was sent to Texas and then Honduras. U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement says an immigration judge ordered Lopez Belloza deported in 2015. But her attorney says she wasn’t aware of any removal order.
link_metadata.title: College freshman deported flying home from Boston for Thanksgiving, despite court order
